{
  "Question": "<p>What can be <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_184\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(0)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>, when <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_185\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(x^{2}+1)=(P(x))^{2}+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_186\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> is polynomial?</p> <p>Let <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_187\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(0)=0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, then <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_188\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(1)=1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_189\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(2)=2\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_190\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(5)=5\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>5</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>5</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_191\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(26)=26\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>26</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>26</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_192\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(677)=677\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>677</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>677</mn> </mrow> </math></span> ... and so on. Then <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_193\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(x)=x\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </math></span>, because all the points on <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_194\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"y=P(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> are <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_195\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"y=x\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </math></span>.</p> <p>If <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_196\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(0)=2\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, then <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_197\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(x)=(x^{2}+1)^{2}+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> for the same reason.</p> <p>But when <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_198\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(0)=3\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>3</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, we have that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_199\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\lim_{x\u2192\u221e}\\log_{x}P(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <munder> <mo movablelimits=\"false\">lim</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u00e2</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u0086</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u0092</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u00e2</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u0088</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u009e</mi> </mrow> </munder> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mi>log</mi> <mi>x</mi> </msub> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mi>P</mi> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> does not converge into an integer. So I think <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_200\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> cannot be a polynomial.</p> <p>Then what are the values of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_201\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(0)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> that makes <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_202\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> polynomial?</p>",
  "Title": "What can be P(0), when <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_183\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P(x^{2}+1)=(P(x))^{2}+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> and P(x) is polynomial?",
  "Tags": "polynomials"
